title: Gaga: Five Foot Two
description: Follow pop provocateur Lady Gaga as she releases a new album, preps for her Super Bowl halftime show, and confronts physical and emotional struggles.

title: Gene Doctors
description: Doctors, scientists and patients shed light on recent breakthroughs in gene therapy and efforts to tackle the root causes of hereditary diseases.

title: Generation Startup
description: This film tracks six young Detroit entrepreneurs over 17 months as they struggle to make their business dreams into successful startup realities.

title: George Harrison: Living in the Material World
description: Director Martin Scorsese profiles former Beatle George Harrison in this reverent portrait that mixes interviews and archival footage.

title: Get Me Roger Stone
description: Examine the rise, fall and rebirth of political operative Roger Stone, who's been an influential member of Team Trump for decades.

title: Ghost of the Mountains
description: An international group of filmmakers sets out on a mission to get up close and personal with a family of elusive snow leopards.

title: Ghostheads
description: Superfans of the monster 1984 hit "Ghostbusters" indulge their passion by gearing up, congregating at conventions and even doing charity work.
actors: Dan Aykroyd, Ivan Reitman, Sigourney Weaver, Ernie Hudson

title: God Knows Where I Am
description: Through diary entries, this documentary follows the life and death of homeless woman Linda Bishop and her struggles with starvation, sanity and God.

title: Great Wild North
description: The hardy men and women who perform highly dangerous work as winter fur trappers in Alaska and the Yukon are profiled in this documentary series.

title: Gringo: The Dangerous Life of John McAfee
description: Tech tycoon John McAfee made millions from his anti-virus software. Now, he may be best known for his bizarre and scandalous lifestyle.
